//  Experiment_1.1 Contains duplicate-I (Leetcode-217)

AIM - Given an integer array nums, return true if any value appears at least twice
       in the array, and return false if every element is distinct.

ALGORITHM:
1. Sort the array nums.
2. For i = 0 to nums.size() - 2
      If nums[i] == nums[i + 1]
            Return true
3. Return false


Code:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsDuplicate(vector<int>& nums) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.size() - 1; i++) {
            if (nums[i] == nums[i + 1]) {
                return true;
            }
        }

        return false;
        
    }
}; 


//  Experiment_1.2 Contains duplicate-II (Leetcode-219)

AIM: Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return true if there are two distinct
      indices i and j in the array such that nums[i] == nums[j] and abs(i - j) <= k.

ALGORITHM:
1. Create an empty hash map lastIndex to store each element and its most recent index.
2. Traverse the array from left to right.
3. For each element nums[i]:
 > Check if it already exists in the hash map.
 > If it exists, calculate the distance between the current index and the previous index.
 > If i - lastIndex[nums[i]] <= k, return true.
4. Update the current index of the element in the hash map.
5. If the traversal finishes without finding such a pair, return false.

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsNearbyDuplicate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        unordered_map<int, int> mp;

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            if (mp.find(nums[i]) != mp.end()) {
                if (i - mp[nums[i]] <= k) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
            mp[nums[i]] = i;
        }

        return false;
    }
}; 
